---
// Standing crisis-support block at the foot of an article. Layout-
// rendered, frontmatter-driven (post.data.crisisResources). The author
// NEVER writes this block into the body — duplication would guarantee
// drift, and one day a piece that should carry it wouldn't.
//
// Single source of copy. US / 988 only for now. If the publication
// ever needs non-US resources, add an optional `region`/locale prop
// and key the strings on it.
//
// Deliberately does NOT promise confidentiality or "no police
// involvement" — those vary by circumstance and a published page
// should not assure what it cannot guarantee.
---

<aside class="crisis-resources" aria-label="Crisis support resources">
  <h2 class="crisis-resources__heading">If you need to talk to someone</h2>
  <p class="crisis-resources__body">
    If you're having thoughts of suicide or self-harm, you don't have to sit with them alone. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide &amp; Crisis Lifeline and talk with a trained counselor, any hour. Chat is also available at <a class="crisis-resources__link" href="https://988lifeline.org">988lifeline.org</a>.
  </p>
</aside>

<style>
  .crisis-resources {
    max-width: 480px;
    margin: 2.5rem auto;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .crisis-resources__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
  }

  .crisis-resources__body {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .crisis-resources__link {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
  }

  .crisis-resources__link:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
